    </edge>
    <data key="d0">Marathon Oil Drone Imagery Processing</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ww5fiyF6eg</data>
    <data key="d2">Marathon Oil leverages a serverless architecture to automate the processing and accessibility of drone imagery collected for routine monitoring of well pads. This system helps identify equipment issues, facilitate preventative maintenance, and provide overall health checks. The solution involves third-party drone operations and initial image processing, followed by an AWS-based ingestion pipeline using CloudWatch, Step Functions, and Lambda to store imagery in S3 and create raster proxies for on-premise consumption via Storage Gateway.</data>
    <data key="d3">data_ingestion, interactive, compute_intensive</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
</graphml>
